properties.headline: Lakeshore Flood Watch issued February 11 at 2:18PM CST until February 13 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Chicago IL
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Chicago has issued a Lakeshore
Flood Watch...which is in effect from Thursday morning through
Thursday evening.

* WHAT...Significant lakeshore flooding is possible. Strong north
to north-northwest winds of 25 to 30 mph with gusts up to 35 mph
will build waves to 10 to 14 feet with occasional waves up to 18
feet.

* WHERE...Shoreline areas of Lake and Porter Counties in indiana.

* WHEN...Thursday morning through Thursday evening.

* IMPACTS...The winds and large battering waves combined with
record high lake levels could exacerbate already significant
beach and shoreline erosion sustained in the past several
months. Vulnerable structures along the shore may be heavily
damaged.
properties.instruction:
A Lakeshore Flood Watch means that conditions favorable for
lakeshore flooding are expected to develop. Residents on or near
the shore should take action to protect property...and listen for
later statements or warnings.

NWSheadline: LAKESHORE FLOOD WATCH IN EFFECT FROM THURSDAY MORNING THROUGH THURSDAY EVENING
